1. *Shvaćaš* li koliko mi je važno da se ovo dogodi? (Do you understand how important this is for me?)
2. Ja *shvatam* da ti to nije bila namera. (I understand that it wasn't your intention.)
3. Oni ne *shvaćaju* koliko je ovo ozbiljna situacija. (They don't understand how serious this situation is.)
4. *Shvaćam* da sam pogrešio i izvinjavam se. (I realize I made a mistake and apologize.)
5. Kada *shvatiš* koliko si pogrešio, biće kasno za ispravku. (When you realize how much you've messed up, it will be too late for a correction.)
6. Molim te da *shvatiš* koliko je ovo važno za mene. (Please understand how important this is for me.)
7. *Shvatio* sam da sam propustio tvoj poziv. (I realized that I missed your call.)
8. Da li *shvaćaš* šta ti govorim? (Do you understand what I'm saying?)
9. Oni neće *shvatiti* koliko je ovo bitno dok se ne suoče sa posledicama. (They won't understand how important this is until they face the consequences.)
10. Kada bi ljudi *shvatili* koliko su male stvari bitne, svet bi bio bolje mesto. (If people understood how important small things are, the world would be a better place.)

(Note: The word "shvaćaš" is a form of the verb "shvatiti", which means "to understand". The translations are not always literal but aim to convey the meaning of the sentence.)